  "text": "Associations with the different BP varia bles differed over the study. SBP and PP levels tended to increase over time, whereas DBP levels did not. Among the BP varia bles, PP has been regarded as a stronger predic tor of adverse cardiac outcomes, especially in hypertensive patients [CITATION_1] . Several studies have investigated associations between air pollu tion and BP, but only a few of them have examined PP [CITATION_2] [CITATION_3] . Our findings also indicated wide variation among individual study participants, with SBP or PP increasing by > 10 mmHg after relocation to the urban campus in some cases. This suggests that sus ceptibility to the effects of air pollu tants may vary substantially among individuals in the general population.",
